7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Adobe Firefly and Deep Dream Generator share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Image, Image To Image, Style Transfer. Where Adobe Firefly pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Inpainting and Outpainting and Api Access and Commercial License, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Adobe Firefly holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Deep Dream Generator scores 4/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Adobe Firefly and Deep Dream Generator offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Adobe Firefly's free tier and Deep Dream Generator's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
