b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Adobe Firefly is best suited for commercial projects, designers, Adobe workflow, safe content, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Deep Dream Generator, meanwhile, shines for artistic effects, style transfer, surreal art, creative experimentation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Adobe Firefly describes itself as \"Adobe's commercially safe AI image generator trained on licensed content.\" Deep Dream Generator, established in 2015, positions itself as \"AI art generator known for surreal and psychedelic visual styles.\" With 8 years between them, Deep Dream Generator brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Adobe Firefly offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Adobe Firefly** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 4.0), more features (7 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Deep Dream Generator is a poor choice — far from it. Deep Dream Generator excels in its own right, particularly for artistic effects and style transfer.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value trained on licensed content, safe for commercial use, go with Adobe Firefly. If unique artistic styles not found elsewhere matters more to you, Deep Dream Generator is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
